      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَشْتَرِي اَلْجُلُودَ مِنَ اَلْقَصَّابِ فَيُعْطِيهِ كُلَّ يَوْمٍ شَيْئاً مَعْلُوماً فَقَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3940 - It is narrated from Hadid bin Hakim, who said:\nI said to Abu Abdillah (as): \"A man buys hides from a butcher and pays him a fixed amount every day.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in that.\""
        ]
      }
